{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17612792","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17612792"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:28:35+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:28:35+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16289"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16289","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16289"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0,0.54,0.31,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8980"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115944"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8980","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8980"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16289"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97943"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5586"},{"type":"tags","id":"7184"},{"type":"tags","id":"7197"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21366"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21372"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115944","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115944"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe stapedius is a small muscle in the middle ear that attaches to the stapes (stirrup) bone. It contracts in response to loud sounds as part of the acoustic reflex.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following cranial nerves provides motor innervation to the stapedius muscle?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Trigeminal nerve (V)","Abducens nerve (VI)","Facial nerve (VII)","Vestibulocochlear nerve (VIII)","Glossopharyngeal nerve (IX)"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Efacial nerve (VII)\u003C/strong\u003E provides motor innervation to the stapedius muscle through its stapedial branch. This allows the stapedius to contract and dampen loud sounds by pulling on the stapes bone, protecting the inner ear from acoustic trauma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etrigeminal nerve (V)\u003C/strong\u003E provides sensory innervation to the face and motor innervation to muscles of mastication. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eabducens nerve (VI)\u003C/strong\u003E innervates the lateral rectus muscle of the eye. The \u003Cstrong\u003Evestibulocochlear nerve (VIII)\u003C/strong\u003E carries sensory information for hearing and balance. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eglossopharyngeal nerve (IX)\u003C/strong\u003E provides sensory and motor innervation to the throat and tongue. The tensor tympani, the other middle ear muscle, is innervated by the mandibular branch of the trigeminal nerve.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The stapedius muscle is innervated by cranial nerve VII (facial nerve).","The stapedius muscle dampens loud sounds by pulling on the stapes bone, protecting the inner ear from acoustic trauma."],"references":["Gupta S, Mends F, Hagiwara M, Fatterpekar G, Roehm PC. Imaging the facial nerve: a contemporary review. Radiol Res Pract. 2013;2013:248039. doi: 10.1155/2013/248039. Epub 2013 May 23. PMID: 23766904; PMCID: PMC3676972.","Prasad KC, Azeem Mohiyuddin SM, Anjali PK, Harshita TR, Indu Varsha G, Brindha HS. Microsurgical Anatomy of Stapedius Muscle: Anatomy Revisited, Redefined with Potential Impact in Surgeries. Indian J Otolaryngol Head Neck Surg. 2019 Mar;71(1):14-18. doi: 10.1007/s12070-018-1510-5. Epub 2018 Oct 9. PMID: 30906706; PMCID: PMC6401039.","Netter, F. H. (2015). Netter\u0027s Cranial Nerve Collection E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97943"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16289"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97943","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97943"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-26T16:06:30+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-26T16:09:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8980"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115944"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4930","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4930"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Nervous System"